all year round...

26
00:03:28,770 --> 00:03:31,180
A robot can't catch a cold.

27
00:03:31,930 --> 00:03:33,730
Please do not concern yourself.

28
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:36,310
You won't catch a cold,

29
00:03:36,870 --> 00:03:39,640
but aren't you feeling a little
under the weather?

30
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:42,380
You've been working non-stop
the past few days.

31
00:03:42,770 --> 00:03:44,330
An occasional trip to a hot springs...

32
00:03:44,620 --> 00:03:48,640
Won't work, but how about
soaking yourself in oil?

33
00:03:50,380 --> 00:03:51,540
Otose-sama.

34
00:03:53,170 --> 00:03:57,110
Thank you very much for always
being concerned about me.

35
00:03:58,550 --> 00:04:00,470
But I'm truly fine.

36
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:04,520
The fact that I'm able to work
here with everyone...

37
00:04:05,040 --> 00:04:07,450
The fact that I can be
here with everyone...

38
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:11,290
Is enough to make me happy.

39
00:04:13,770 --> 00:04:19,680
["Smooth Polygons Smooth Men's Hearts Too"]

40
00:04:22,490 --> 00:04:25,030
Eh? Something's wrong with Tama?

41
00:04:25,030 --> 00:04:28,940
Yes... It may have just been
the light playing tricks on me,

42
00:04:29,270 --> 00:04:32,200
but her face looked odd for a moment.

43
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:33,990
Her face looked odd for a moment?

44
00:04:33,990 --> 00:04:36,510
Better than looking odd 24/7.

45
00:04:36,510 --> 00:04:37,580
That's right.

46
00:04:37,580 --> 00:04:42,290
It beats having a face that looks like
a cicada husk 24/7 the way you do.

47
00:04:42,650 --> 00:04:46,260
It reminded me of those fighting games
from a while back, all jagged...

48
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:48,080
What were they called again?

49
00:04:48,670 --> 00:04:49,960
Polygons?

50
00:04:49,960 --> 00:04:53,830
Yes, yes. Her face was all jagged
like it was made of polygons.

51
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:57,640
I'm sure she's tired after working so hard.

52
00:04:58,030 --> 00:05:01,170
Could you check if any screws
are loose or anything?

53
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:06,130
First, you should go see a doctor
for the screws loose in your head.

54
00:05:06,390 --> 00:05:09,700
How could a little breakdown make
a puppet look like polygons?

55
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:11,230
How could a machine get tired?

56
00:05:11,850 --> 00:05:14,180
I saw it with my own eyes.

57
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:18,800
H-Hey...

58
00:05:19,350 --> 00:05:22,160
What's with your face...

59
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,540
What do you mean?

60
00:05:23,540 --> 00:05:25,060
No, it's all jagged.

61
00:05:25,060 --> 00:05:27,220
