65
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:40,460
She has worked too hard
the past few days.

66
00:05:40,730 --> 00:05:44,280
I was worried, so I kept telling
her to take a break.

67
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:46,000
It was probably an optical illusion.

68
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,140
Something that ridiculous
could never happen.

69
00:05:48,140 --> 00:05:50,230
You're the one who's tired.

70
00:05:50,230 --> 00:05:51,550
Your time's coming.

71
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:53,990
I have returned.

72
00:05:53,990 --> 00:05:56,040
Welcome back. Thanks for...

73
00:05:57,250 --> 00:05:58,780
Ah, Master Gintoki.

74
00:05:58,780 --> 00:06:00,340
Good morning.

75
00:06:00,570 --> 00:06:03,700
Forget polygons!
She's down to pixels now!

76
00:06:04,490 --> 00:06:06,290
Tama completed her errand.

77
00:06:06,290 --> 00:06:08,590
230 experience gained.

78
00:06:08,590 --> 00:06:10,610
300 G lost.

79
00:06:10,610 --> 00:06:13,130
Even the speech bubbles
are NES-level!

80
00:06:13,630 --> 00:06:14,810
Otose-sama.

81
00:06:14,810 --> 00:06:16,140
Sorry for the wait.

82
00:06:16,140 --> 00:06:18,190
The supermarket was crowded
because of a sale.

83
00:06:18,190 --> 00:06:20,590
And she's facing forward regardless of
the direction she's moving, like a crab!

84
00:06:20,590 --> 00:06:22,070
The way it was in the first Dragon Quest!

85
00:06:22,070 --> 00:06:23,190
It's creepy!

86
00:06:23,190 --> 00:06:25,720
I can hear that sad song they
played in Radatom Castle!

87
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:27,240
Here, Otose-sama.

88
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,970
These are the goods you requested.

89
00:06:30,260 --> 00:06:32,090
Tama handed over a medicinal herb.

90
00:06:33,650 --> 00:06:36,140
There is no response. It's just a corpse.

91
00:06:33,650 --> 00:06:36,140
[Note: This is a reference to a famous
line from Dragon Quest.]

92
00:06:36,140 --> 00:06:37,340
Who are you calling a "corpse"?!

93
00:06:37,340 --> 00:06:40,340
And I never asked for medicinal herbs!

94
00:06:42,470 --> 00:06:44,500
Tama handed over a cypress stick.

95
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:45,790
I didn't ask for that either!

96
00:06:45,790 --> 00:06:47,900
Which item store did you even go to?!

97
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:49,040
There is no response.

98
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,360
It's just a corpse.

99
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:51,500
Don't try to play dumb!

100
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:52,680
Tama-san!

101
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:53,950
How did you end up like this?!

102
00:06:53,950 --> 00:06:55,950
What in the world happened?!

103
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:57,350
I'm so sorry, Tama!

104
00:06:57,350 --> 00:07:02,720
You must have broken down because
I worked you too hard!

105
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,960
Gin-chan, fix her already.

106
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,740
It's dangerous when she's
all jagged like this.

107
00:07:06,740 --> 00:07:07,850
People will cut themselves.

108
00:07:07,850 --> 00:07:12,320
You should fix her into a form that's
completely round and child safe.

109
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:15,180
What's wrong with leaving her like this?

110
00:07:15,180 --> 00:07:16,650
There isn't that much difference.

111
00:07:16,650 --> 00:07:17,560
Hell yes, there is!

112
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:18,470
Just look!

113
00:07:18,470 --> 00:07:20,660
Her legs are still moving while
she's quietly standing here!

114
00:07:20,660 --> 00:07:21,700
She only has two available poses,

115
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:24,470
one with her right leg up and
one with her left leg up!

116
00:07:24,470 --> 00:07:25,760
It'll be fine.

117
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:27,080
She'll get the pose where

118
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:29,420
[Note: Refers to Princess Laura
from Dragon Quest game.]

119
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:29,420
she's carrying a princess after
she rescues Princess Laura.

120
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:31,630
Princess Laura doesn't exist in this world!

121
00:07:31,970 --> 00:07:35,980
Appearances aside, she
was always this useless.

122
00:07:35,980 --> 00:07:38,710
Who cares if she stays this way?

123
00:07:39,020 --> 00:07:44,480
Besides, you young'uns are too
used to CG and 3D rendering.

124
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,810
Pixels are classic.

125
00:07:46,810 --> 00:07:48,880
Uh, what are you talking about?

126
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:53,380
Back in our day, we couldn't
wait to explore dungeons

127
00:07:53,380 --> 00:07:55,980
that consisted of just straight lines.

128
00:07:55,980 --> 00:08:00,900
There wasn't any pretty CG, but we
let our imaginations run the show.

129
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:03,920
Uh, so what are you talking about?

130
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:07,230
Sure, the first time I turned the power on,

131
00:08:07,230 --> 00:08:09,520
I was a little disappointed with the flashy cover
art not matching the actual in-game screens.

132
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:11,170
I was like, that's it?

133
00:08:11,170 --> 00:08:15,590
But by the time I reached the ending
credits, I felt like I was the hero!

134
00:08:15,590 --> 00:08:17,710
I was so touched when I saw the
word "you" in the cast credits.

135
00:08:17,710 --> 00:08:19,190
Uh, what are you...

136
00:08:19,190 --> 00:08:24,540
But nowadays, they play these
long-ass CG cut scenes.

137
00:08:24,540 --> 00:08:26,590
Are we trying to watch a movie?

138
00:08:26,590 --> 00:08:27,580
No, right?

139
00:08:27,580 --> 00:08:29,980
We want to play a game!

140
00:08:29,980 --> 00:08:30,940
No!

141
00:08:30,940 --> 00:08:33,180
How did this turn into a discussion
about gaming?!

142
00:08:33,460 --> 00:08:34,630
Got it?

143
00:08:34,630 --> 00:08:37,340
Games don't play you! You play games!

144
00:08:37,340 --> 00:08:38,870
We don't need any CG or movies!

145
00:08:38,870 --> 00:08:40,600
You wanna let them lead you around?!

146
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:42,330
Do you have no imagination?!

147
00:08:42,330 --> 00:08:43,770
Pixel graphics!

148
00:08:43,770 --> 00:08:45,770
Events that are text-only!

149
00:08:45,770 --> 00:08:47,920
That's all you need!

150
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:49,160
That's enough. Just shut up.

151
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:52,870
The Wizardry generation can go scour
their dungeons for Muramasa.

152
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:52,870
[Note: Wizardry was a 1980s game. Swords
named Muramasa often show up in games.]

153
00:08:53,170 --> 00:08:55,120
You probably don't think you can fix her.

154
00:08:55,460 --> 00:08:57,710
I get it. I won't ask you.

155
00:08:57,710 --> 00:08:59,080
Pathetic.

156
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:02,230
As pathetic as a man who can't
hook up a DVD player.

157
00:09:02,230 --> 00:09:05,780
As pathetic as a man who screams
when he sees a cockroach.

158
00:09:05,780 --> 00:09:10,090
As pathetic as a man who still has
his mommy buy his underwear.

159
00:09:10,090 --> 00:09:12,260
Seriously, what's with the adults
who get all nostalgic

160
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:14,840
when they start talking about games?

161
00:09:15,940 --> 00:09:17,760
Tama handed over a medicinal herb.

162
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:19,390
Why are you trying to be nice to me?!

163
00:09:19,390 --> 00:09:21,530
What kind of wounds am I supposed
to heal with that?!

164
00:09:21,910 --> 00:09:24,780
Hey, you shouldn't look down
on the Wizardry generation.

165
00:09:24,780 --> 00:09:27,650
I could fix this in a second if I wanted to.

166
00:09:28,850 --> 00:09:32,240
Fine. If you're gonna be that way, fine.

167
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:33,380
I'll fix her.

168
00:09:33,380 --> 00:09:34,910
Really?

169
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:36,520
Just watch, polygon generation.

170
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:39,970
I'll show you the power of
the Wizardry generation.

171
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:47,760
Huh? What's with the screen?

172
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:49,940
