179
00:09:57,940 --> 00:09:59,470
All right!

180
00:09:59,470 --> 00:10:01,610
You didn't fix anything!

181
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:06,260
Why are you trying to go through
events text-only like in Wizardry?!

182
00:10:06,260 --> 00:10:08,980
You think it's okay to use
only text in an anime?!

183
00:10:08,980 --> 00:10:10,340
The screen won't last!

184
00:10:10,340 --> 00:10:11,920
You can't fix anything like that!

185
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:14,850
I gave the viewers the freedom
to imagine how she was fixed.

186
00:10:14,850 --> 00:10:16,750
That's the Wizardry way.

187
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:18,610
You're just being lazy!

188
00:10:18,610 --> 00:10:19,910
And she isn't fixed!

189
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:20,780
Forget it!

190
00:10:20,780 --> 00:10:22,210
The Wizardry generation can go

191
00:10:22,210 --> 00:10:23,710
and fail to resurrect at a church
and turn to ashes!

192
00:10:23,710 --> 00:10:25,310
Zip it, polygon generation!

193
00:10:25,310 --> 00:10:27,940
Fail to resurrect at a church and
turn into powdered polygons!

194
00:10:27,940 --> 00:10:28,530
Shut up!

195
00:10:28,530 --> 00:10:31,030
Teleport into a rock and
wipe out the party!

196
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:35,740
You teleport into polygons and live
on for me as a Virtua Fighter!

197
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:39,240
[Mechanic's Shop]

198
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,000
She's got a cold.

199
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:44,830
A cold?

200
00:10:44,830 --> 00:10:47,040
How can a robot catch a cold?

201
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:52,080
It would be more accurate to say that
she's caught a computer virus.

202
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:53,570
A computer virus?

203
00:10:55,590 --> 00:11:01,320
An illegal program that roams the
virtual world destroying data.

204
00:11:01,890 --> 00:11:09,070
She was probably infected when she connected
to the Internet for her work.

205
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:14,490
So the computer virus has destroyed
Tama-san's program,

206
00:11:14,490 --> 00:11:16,400
which is why she's behaving this way.

207
00:11:17,180 --> 00:11:18,370
Hey now.

208
00:11:18,370 --> 00:11:20,780
We finally recovered from our colds,

209
00:11:20,780 --> 00:11:22,000
and now this?

210
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,850
Old geezer, you can fix Tama, right?

211
00:11:23,850 --> 00:11:25,440
You can put her back to normal, right?

212
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:32,080
A commercial anti-virus program would
be enough to deal with ordinary viruses,

213
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:35,110
but she's got an especially tough one.

214
00:11:35,870 --> 00:11:38,290
The computer virus "Tapir."

215
00:11:38,290 --> 00:11:44,020
A brand-new virus that infects the program,
consumes it, and multiplies.

216
00:11:44,810 --> 00:11:49,700
Tapir reads the data from
the system it has infected

217
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:52,350
while rewriting its own program.

218
00:11:52,350 --> 00:11:55,330
It evolves, becoming more
efficient as it multiplies

219
00:11:55,330 --> 00:11:59,200
and more deeply embedded in its victim.

220
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:04,640
A Tapir infection caught early
on can be easily dealt with,

221
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:08,790
but one that's been evolving over an extended
period will be more difficult to remove.

222
00:12:09,470 --> 00:12:15,160
And the Tapir virus will be as strong
as the system it has infected.

223
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:20,680
Once it infected Tama, who
is a highly advanced robot,

224
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:23,420
it must have evolved a great deal.

225
00:12:23,420 --> 00:12:26,440
And it's been there for a while.

226
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:31,140
Nobody can do anything about it.

227
00:12:31,340 --> 00:12:34,930
It's evolved into the strongest
and worst virus ever.

228
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,530
N-No way...

229
00:12:41,210 --> 00:12:43,690
Even you, Gengai-san, can't fix her...

230
00:12:43,690 --> 00:12:45,790
Don't be ridiculous.

231
00:12:45,790 --> 00:12:48,360
I'm the top robot technician in Edo.

232
00:12:48,790 --> 00:12:50,590
There's nothing I can't do.

233
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:53,150
However...

234
00:12:53,610 --> 00:12:55,990
We're dealing with a brand-new virus.

235
00:12:55,990 --> 00:12:57,960
It'll take some time to make a vaccine.

236
00:12:57,960 --> 00:13:03,800
By the time I finish, Tama will have
been completely consumed.

237
00:13:06,610 --> 00:13:11,510
She'll be a robot with no soul.

238
00:13:13,430 --> 00:13:14,810
No way...

239
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:21,730
But there's still a way to save Tama.

240
00:13:22,570 --> 00:13:23,840
What?

241
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:25,210
Let us hear it, old geezer.

242
00:13:26,420 --> 00:13:28,420
It'll be a dangerous gamble.

243
00:13:28,660 --> 00:13:30,350
For Tama...

244
00:13:30,860 --> 00:13:33,050
And for all of you...

245
00:13:33,460 --> 00:13:34,670
It doesn't matter.

246
00:13:34,670 --> 00:13:35,920
Just tell us.

247
00:13:36,550 --> 00:13:38,180
Should I interpret that response to mean

248
00:13:38,180 --> 00:13:41,790
that you're willing to risk
your lives for Tama?

249
00:13:42,410 --> 00:13:44,120
Think what you will.

250
00:13:44,540 --> 00:13:46,280
Just tell us already.

251
00:13:53,710 --> 00:13:55,510
Huh? What's this?

252
00:13:56,390 --> 00:13:58,550
What's this robot doing?

253
00:13:59,020 --> 00:14:00,650
Hey, what's it...

254
00:14:12,470 --> 00:14:14,290
Gin-chan!!

255
00:14:14,290 --> 00:14:16,970
Wh-Wh-What are you doing, Gengai-san?!

256
00:14:16,970 --> 00:14:20,270
Th-This is more than just risking his life!

257
00:14:20,870 --> 00:14:23,050
Th-This means Gin-san's...

258
00:14:23,050 --> 00:14:25,070
This... This is...!

259
00:14:41,430 --> 00:14:43,270
Huh? What's this?

260
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:46,040
Who is this?

261
00:14:46,270 --> 00:14:47,390
I don't like this.

262
00:14:47,610 --> 00:14:49,350
G-Gengai-san?!

263
00:14:49,350 --> 00:14:50,720
What is this?!

264
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:53,310
Why is Gin-san so tiny?!

265
00:14:54,050 --> 00:14:57,580
The magic mallet Z503.

266
00:14:54,050 --> 00:14:57,580
[Note: Parody of legendary Japanese
hammer, Uchide-no-Kozuchi.]

267
00:14:57,580 --> 00:15:00,900
It sends super magnetic waves
through the object it hits

268
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:05,030
and shrinks the target's cells
and the target itself.

269
00:15:05,030 --> 00:15:08,200
A high-tech weapon created by yours truly.

270
00:15:12,580 --> 00:15:13,910
You're joking, right?

271
00:15:14,170 --> 00:15:15,500
I'm wrong, right?

272
00:15:15,770 --> 00:15:18,000
Don't tell me you're going
to smash us with...

273
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,490
S-Stop!

274
00:15:19,490 --> 00:15:21,450
Don't add to your crimes!

275
00:15:21,450 --> 00:15:23,870
What can you possibly accomplish
by doing this?!

276
00:15:23,870 --> 00:15:25,550
Why are you doing this?!

277
00:15:26,090 --> 00:15:28,040
Shouldn't that be obvious?

278
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:30,190
We're going to eliminate the virus.

279
00:15:30,190 --> 00:15:33,400
Not through a vaccine or an anti-virus.

280
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:37,080
You midgets are doing it.

281
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:40,970
Best of luck to you.

282
00:15:43,730 --> 00:15:46,690
You jerk!

283
00:16:12,020 --> 00:16:13,030
Gin-san.

284
00:16:13,330 --> 00:16:15,550
Can we trade off already?

285
00:16:15,550 --> 00:16:16,640
Don't give me that crap.

286
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:18,530
We just switched.

287
00:16:18,530 --> 00:16:20,120
Once you're old,

288
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:24,240
[Note: Parody of Book Off, a
chain of used bookstores.]

289
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:22,890
you'll be willing to buy back the hardships
during your youth at a Book-Hoff.

290
00:16:22,890 --> 00:16:24,240
Even if they're used.

291
00:16:25,820 --> 00:16:28,540
It's extremely tiring to row through oil.

292
00:16:28,540 --> 00:16:29,800
I'm hungry.

293
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:32,120
You think any half-eaten
food will float by?

294
00:16:32,120 --> 00:16:34,580
No, robots don't eat food.

295
00:16:34,580 --> 00:16:36,800
Where are we right now?

296
00:16:37,010 --> 00:16:38,670
We entered through her mouth,

297
00:16:38,670 --> 00:16:40,120
so we're probably somewhere
around the stomach.

298
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:42,480
Does a robot even have a stomach?

299
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:43,560
I don't know.

300
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:46,940
Where are we even headed
to begin with?

301
00:16:47,290 --> 00:16:48,220
I don't know.

302
00:16:48,220 --> 00:16:50,590
How can you not know?!
What are we supposed to do?!

303
00:16:50,590 --> 00:16:53,210
He turns us into midgets all of a sudden,
tells us to defeat the virus,

304
00:16:53,210 --> 00:16:54,860
and throws us into her mouth?!

305
00:16:54,860 --> 00:16:58,660
We don't know how to defeat
the virus or where it even is!

306
00:16:58,660 --> 00:17:00,430
Don't take it out on me.

307
00:17:00,430 --> 00:17:02,240
This is all Gengai-san's fault.

308
00:17:02,950 --> 00:17:04,460
That stupid old man...

309
00:17:08,690 --> 00:17:10,570
Why am I the only one with two?

310
00:17:11,050 --> 00:17:12,230
Well?

311
00:17:12,230 --> 00:17:14,700
I call it Operation Midget.

312
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:15,550
That's so bland.

313
00:17:15,550 --> 00:17:16,460
Use a little more imagination.

314
00:17:16,460 --> 00:17:23,290
You're going to enter Tama's body
and treat her from the inside.

315
00:17:23,510 --> 00:17:24,640
Uh...

316
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:28,610
We don't know anything about
robots, so what do we do?

317
00:17:28,610 --> 00:17:30,200
I was expecting you to ask that.

318
00:17:30,430 --> 00:17:33,030
Use these. Here.

319
00:17:34,410 --> 00:17:36,640
Isn't this just a toothpick?!

320
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:39,980
Old geezer! You sure you didn't
just want to play with midgets?!

321
00:17:39,980 --> 00:17:41,810
Don't mistake those for
ordinary toothpicks.

322
00:17:41,810 --> 00:17:43,780
They've been modified.

323
00:17:43,780 --> 00:17:46,320
Gin-no-ji, push on the base
of your toothpick.

324
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:47,890
Eh?

325
00:17:47,890 --> 00:17:50,500
Like we can count on your modifications
to be worth anything.

326
00:17:50,500 --> 00:17:51,800
The last time...

327
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:54,340
Gin-no-ji! Push on your
wooden sword's grip!

328
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:58,820
It dispenses soy sauce.

329
00:17:58,820 --> 00:18:00,720
So, why soy sauce?!

330
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:01,780
Don't worry.

331
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:04,910
My technical skills have
improved since then.

332
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:06,870
Go ahead. Push it.

333
00:18:06,870 --> 00:18:09,440
Tch, I'm not expecting anything...

334
00:18:10,120 --> 00:18:12,860
But I'll give it a shot!

335
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:16,110
It's dashi soy sauce.

336
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:16,110
[Note: Dashi is bonito fish stock.]

337
00:18:16,110 --> 00:18:18,300
How have your technical skills
improved, stupid old geezer?!

338
00:18:18,300 --> 00:18:21,530
Woohoo! My egg rice will be tastier now!

339
00:18:21,530 --> 00:18:23,830
Shut up! You turn into soy sauce!

340
00:18:23,830 --> 00:18:25,820
Stop griping and get going.

341
00:18:28,930 --> 00:18:30,580
Hey! Why a bowl?!

342
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:33,470
You just want to play with midgets!

343
00:18:33,470 --> 00:18:35,220
It's important to have atmosphere.

344
00:18:35,220 --> 00:18:38,510
It's all sticky.

345
00:18:38,510 --> 00:18:41,570
This must be some kind of special
coating to make it easier

346
00:18:41,570 --> 00:18:43,870
to enter Tama-san's body...

347
00:18:43,870 --> 00:18:46,170
It's the bowl I just used to eat natto.

348
00:18:43,870 --> 00:18:46,170
[Note: Natto is fermented soybeans.]

349
00:18:46,170 --> 00:18:47,990
I'm gonna strangle you!

350
00:18:48,230 --> 00:18:49,910
You'll be going through the mouth.

351
00:18:50,380 --> 00:18:52,160
Godspeed, you three.

352
00:18:55,930 --> 00:18:57,470
Damn old geezer...

353
00:18:57,470 --> 00:19:00,080
What are we supposed
to do with a toothpick?!

354
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:02,220
It can't even remove the squid
stuck between my teeth...

355
00:19:02,220 --> 00:19:03,010
Hey, it got it.

356
00:19:03,010 --> 00:19:04,240
It's actually useful!

357
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:05,330
Thanks, old geezer!

358
00:19:05,330 --> 00:19:06,620
Like I'm actually going to say that!

359
00:19:06,620 --> 00:19:08,060
Die, you damn old fart!

360
00:19:08,060 --> 00:19:09,500
Choke on some squid and die!

361
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:13,790
Pulling out some Do***mon-esque
gadget and shoving us into hell!

362
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:13,790
[Note: Parody of Doraemon.]

363
00:19:13,790 --> 00:19:16,730
If I ever get out of here, I'm going inside
him and exiting through his urethra

364
00:19:16,730 --> 00:19:19,290
while slashing this toothpick around!

365
00:19:19,290 --> 00:19:21,260
Yeah, yeah. That's enough whining.

366
00:19:21,510 --> 00:19:24,190
This is the only way to save Tama-san.

367
00:19:24,190 --> 00:19:26,320
We don't have a choice.

368
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:27,680
That's right.

369
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:29,840
Nothing ventured, nothing gained.

370
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:31,270
You can't reach the urinary uvula

371
00:19:31,270 --> 00:19:33,110
without passing through
the palatine uvula.

372
00:19:33,110 --> 00:19:35,260
Uh, Tama-san doesn't have one.

373
00:19:35,260 --> 00:19:36,730
But her name means "balls."

374
00:19:36,730 --> 00:19:37,520
Get over it!

375
00:19:38,460 --> 00:19:40,120
I can see land!

376
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:41,590
I wonder where we are.

377
00:19:41,590 --> 00:19:44,310
We entered through the mouth and
passed through the stomach,

378
00:19:44,310 --> 00:19:46,560
so we're probably near the entrance
to the small intestine.

379
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:48,770
Does a robot even have
a small intestine?

380
00:19:48,770 --> 00:19:49,780
I don't know.

381
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:56,110
Will this really work?

382
00:19:56,110 --> 00:19:59,070
We'll just have to look around.

383
00:19:59,430 --> 00:20:02,330
We can enter the small intestine
and head towards the anus.

384
00:20:02,330 --> 00:20:04,490
And does a robot even have an anus?

385
00:20:04,490 --> 00:20:05,270
I don't know.

386
00:20:06,040 --> 00:20:07,820
We don't have a choice.

387
00:20:07,820 --> 00:20:11,290
It's not like we can gather information when
there aren't any people around...

388
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:16,550
There's one!

389
00:20:16,550 --> 00:20:17,740
There's someone here!

390
00:20:17,740 --> 00:20:18,550
Why?!

391
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:20,870
Why is there a person inside Tama-san?!

392
00:20:20,870 --> 00:20:23,080
And why is he wearing a bodysuit?!

393
00:20:23,080 --> 00:20:25,490
I don't really get it, but I'll take
whatever I can get right now.

394
00:20:25,490 --> 00:20:27,150
We can ask him.

395
00:20:27,150 --> 00:20:27,900
Hold on!

396
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:29,170
Gin-san! It's dangerous!

397
00:20:29,450 --> 00:20:31,280
Uh, excuse me.

398
00:20:31,870 --> 00:20:34,990
Uh, sorry to disturb your nap,

399
00:20:34,990 --> 00:20:37,630
but I need to ask a few questions.

400
00:20:37,630 --> 00:20:40,320
Uh, do you live here?

401
00:20:40,320 --> 00:20:43,790
We're on a company trip and
this is our first time here,

402
00:20:43,790 --> 00:20:45,290
so we don't know our way around.

403
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:49,520
Uh, excuse me...

404
00:20:49,870 --> 00:20:51,940
There's an arrow sticking
out of your rear...

405
00:20:51,940 --> 00:20:52,760
Are you okay?

406
00:20:53,330 --> 00:20:54,940
Greetings, travelers.

407
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:59,010
Fortune must be smiling on me to bring me an
encounter with you as I lie on my deathbed.

408
00:20:59,010 --> 00:21:02,260
Lie on your deathbed? You just
have an arrow in your ass.

409
00:21:02,260 --> 00:21:06,850
Please listen to my last request.

410
00:21:06,850 --> 00:21:08,680
Uh, could you listen to me first?

411
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:10,990
It's just an arrow in your ass.

412
00:21:11,530 --> 00:21:14,490
I bequeath you to carry
a message to my king.

413
00:21:14,490 --> 00:21:15,280
King?

414
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:18,730
It saddens me to say that
our leukocyte army

415
00:21:18,730 --> 00:21:20,860
has fallen to the virus army.

416
00:21:21,310 --> 00:21:25,500
This world will soon fall into
the hands of the Tapir.

417
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:29,610
I pray that our king takes flight.

418
00:21:31,460 --> 00:21:37,570
And searches for the legendary
warriors from another world...

419
00:21:38,390 --> 00:21:41,550
Search for the midgets...

420
00:21:44,490 --> 00:21:46,990
[To Be Continued]

421
00:23:17,040 --> 00:23:21,500
[A Little 3-Z Ginpachi Sensei]

422
00:23:18,130 --> 00:23:19,130
A Little

423
00:23:19,130 --> 00:23:21,290
Ginpachi Sensei!

424
00:23:22,060 --> 00:23:23,890
Uh, we have a question from

425
00:23:23,890 --> 00:23:26,220
someone with the pen name
Cherry Blossom Samurai.

426
00:23:26,220 --> 00:23:28,000
Hello.

427
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:31,220
I'm having a hard time drawing
Gin-san's dead fish eyes.

428
00:23:31,220 --> 00:23:33,020
Please tell me if there's a trick to it.

429
00:23:33,430 --> 00:23:35,920
Okay. Here's your answer.

430
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:39,780
Basically, you need to separate
the eyebrows from the eyes.

431
00:23:40,950 --> 00:23:42,950
And draw heavy eyelids.

432
00:23:42,950 --> 00:23:46,220
You should only be able
to see half of his pupils.

433
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:48,310
Okay, all done.

434
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:52,160
Then you bring the eyebrows
and eyes closer together

435
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:53,920
and sharpen the eyelids.

436
00:23:55,030 --> 00:23:57,670
There you go. A serious-looking Gin-san.

437
00:23:58,340 --> 00:24:00,260
Okay, Cherry Blossom Samurai.

438
00:24:00,650 --> 00:24:04,720
Stop trying to escape the lecture
by doodling in class.

439
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:15,470
[Preview]

440
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:06,710
Hey!

441
00:24:06,710 --> 00:24:10,110
There's an RPG world
inside Tama's body?!

442
00:24:10,110 --> 00:24:12,490
Why do leukocytes, white blood cells,
have a king?!

443
00:24:12,490 --> 00:24:14,890
Why does this look so much
like Dragon Quest?!

444
00:24:14,890 --> 00:24:16,100
I don't know.

445
00:24:16,480 --> 00:24:17,580
The next episode...

446
00:24:17,580 --> 00:24:19,170
"The Human Body is Like
a Little Universe!"

447
00:24:20,020 --> 00:24:23,810
[An RPG world of anti-leukocyte viruses
has emerged within Tama's body.]

448
00:24:23,810 --> 00:24:29,940
[Gin-san and the gang set out for the castle
in order to meet with the Leukocyte King.]

449
00:24:29,940 --> 00:24:34,810
[See you next time.]
